-- BNP pleads guilty, agrees to forfeit $8.8 bln in sanctions case
-- By Joseph Ax
-- Mon Jun 30, 2014 04:18PM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, June 30 (Reuters) - BNP Paribas <BNPP.PA> on Monday pleaded guilty to two criminal charges and agreed to forfeit $8.83 billion, as part of a broad investigation into allegations the French bank violated U.S. sanctions laws.

A lawyer for BNP briefly appeared in New York state court on Monday, to answer one count of falsifying business records, and one count of conspiracy.